#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:1
msgid "E0003"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `unused_type_declaration`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:5
msgid "Unused type declaration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:7
msgid ""
"This type is not used by any other part of your code, which means it's "
"not constructed nor consumed, and others can't construct nor consume due "
"to visibility. Type declaration is by default abstract, which means it is"
" publicly visible to users of this package, but they cannot construct nor"
" destruct the type. Therefore, this warning is only shown if the type has"
" abstract or private visibility, and is not constructed nor consumed by "
"any other part of this package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:15
msgid ""
"Note that this warning might uncover other bugs in your code. For "
"example, if there are two types in the package that has similar name, you"
" might just use the other type by mistake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:19
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:21
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"struct Foo {\n"
"  bar : Int\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn f() -> Unit {\n"
"  struct Bar {\n"
"    foot : Int\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:25
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:27
msgid "There are multiple ways to fix this warning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:29
msgid "If the type is indeed useless, you can remove the definition of the type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:30
msgid ""
"If this type is not local, and is part of the public API of your module, "
"you can add `pub` or `pub(all)` visibility keyword from the type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:33
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub struct Foo {\n"
"  bar : Int\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:39
msgid "Check if you are referencing the type with a correct name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0003.md:41
msgid ""
"It is rather rare to have a type that is private and unused at the same "
"time; therefore, we suggest you remove the type if it is not used."
msgstr ""

